# BLESSED TRADER.
**Your guide to consistency in the industry of loss.**

---

## LEFT DIAGRAM - PROTECTED LOW

**Label:** "PROTECTED LOW"

**Annotations:**
- "RUN ON STOPS" (at bottom left)
- "BREAK OF STRUCTURE" (dashed horizontal line at top)
- Boxed area highlighting the low point

**Explanatory text:**
"Price swept the SSLQ expanded higher broke the structure respecting bullish levels (bullish orderflow)."

---

## MIDDLE DIAGRAM - LONG SETUP

**Annotations:**
- "Long at P.D. (Orderblock, FVG, etc.) ONCE CONFIRMED"
- Upward arrow indicating entry direction
- Gray horizontal zones/blocks shown above price action
- Downward arrow pointing to a low
- Triangle/wedge formation visible

---

## RIGHT DIAGRAM - UNPROTECTED LOW

**Label:** "UNPROTECTED LOW"

**Annotations:**
- "Sell-side liquidity (SSLQ)" (horizontal line through middle section)
- Boxed area highlighting a low point
- Gray horizontal zone at top
- Large downward arrow at right side

**Explanatory text:**
"Price been forming small higher lows, equal lows its strong & directional moves, the liquidity is building below it (small lows)."

---

## VISUAL ELEMENTS:
- Three separate chart diagrams showing different market structure scenarios
- Zigzag price action lines throughout
- Rectangular boxes highlighting key price levels
- Dashed lines indicating structural breaks
- Directional arrows showing potential trade directions
- Gray shaded zones representing order blocks or fair value gaps
